answers.body_markdown:
You need to use `raw-loader`.
```
npm install raw-loader --save-dev
```
Then you can import raw `.txt` file like below;
```
import RawText from &#39;raw-loader!./rawText.txt&#39;
```
Or, edit webpack config like below;
```
// webpack.config.js
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.txt$/i,
        use: &#39;raw-loader&#39;,
      },
    ],
  },
};
```
Then you can import like `import RawText from &#39;./rawText.txt&#39;`

For more information -&gt; [webpack-contrib/raw-loader][1]


  [1]: https://github.com/webpack-contrib/raw-loader

